column15: My focus is preparing folks for the 2024 total solar eclipse, But I took time out to visit Fairbanks, Alaska for the winter solstice. I've always wanted to capture a time-lapse of the Sun rising and setting and only getting 2°above the horizon. The arc spans about 44°. Luckily, I had clear weather.
